Dynamic Storage Management in Linux:

Managing storage efficiently is one of the key responsibilities of a Linux system administrator. With the increasing need for flexibility, 
Dynamic Storage Management (DSM) allows administrators to resize, reallocate, and optimize storage on the fly without downtime.

Dynamic Storage Management (DSM) is the ability to adapt storage capacity dynamically based on workload or requirement. Unlike static partitions, DSM allows you to:

Expand or shrink storage volumes
Add or remove disks without downtime
Optimize performance and redundancy

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

DSM is primarily implemented using Logical Volume Management (LVM)

Dynamic storage management flow diagram:

     create volumes on AWS
          |
[Step 1: Create Physical Volume (PV)]
  Command: pvcreate /dev/sdb
          |
          v
[Step 2: Create Volume Group (VG)]
  Command: vgcreate vg_data /dev/sdb
          |
          v
[Step 3: Create Logical Volume (LV)]
  Command: lvcreate -L 10G -n lv_storage vg_data
          |
          v
[Step 4: Format & Mount Volume]
  Command: mkfs.ext4 /dev/vg_data/lv_storage
  Command: mount /dev/vg_data/lv_storage /mnt/storage
          |
          v
[Accessible Storage]
          |
          v
---------------------------------------------------
|           Dynamic Storage Management           |
---------------------------------------------------
[Step 5: Add New Physical Volume (PV)]
  Command: pvcreate /dev/sdc
          |
          v
[Step 6: Extend Volume Group (VG)]
  Command: vgextend vg_data /dev/sdc
          |
          v
[Step 7: Extend Logical Volume (LV)]
  Command: lvextend -L +5G /dev/vg_data/lv_storage
          |
          v
[Step 8: Resize Filesystem]
  Command: resize2fs /dev/vg_data/lv_storage   # For ext4
          |
          v
[Step 9: Optional: Create Snapshot]
  Command: lvcreate -s -L 2G -n lv_snapshot /dev/vg_data/lv_storage
          |
          v
[Step 10: Expanded & Protected Storage Accessible]

---------------------------

Shows initial volume setup (PV → VG → LV → Mount)
Shows dynamic storage operations (add disk, extend VG/LV, resize filesystem)
